      "date": "2014-05-08 22:52:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nI realize that is but one step on a longer path towards user-kernel interface nirvana, and I am at peace with the general approach. I would prefer, though, if the new type names were based on the linux (__u64) types rather than the user space (uint64_t) types.  This keeps it clear that these are kernel data structures, and their use in user space should general be limited to low level libraries.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
