          {
            "commit": "6fcf6581f5bd1cf4ff878b0acc8ecb59cc1a472f",
            "subject": "LU-4961 lustre: remove liblustre.h and obd.h from userspace"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "John L. Hammond",
          "email": "john.hammond@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-05-08 19:17:05.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "John L. Hammond",
          "email": "john.hammond@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-05-08 22:06:28.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-5011 lustre: don't export kernel types to userspace",
        "message": "LU-5011 lustre: don't export kernel types to userspace\n\nRemove libcfs/posix/posix-types.h. Add a new header libcfs/types.h\nwhich defines namespace safe fixed-width types lu_intXX_t and\nlu_uintXX_t for use in packaged headers like lustreapi.h and\nlustre_user.h. Rewrite those headers to use the new types. Including\nthese headers will no longer define the __{s,u}XX types unless Lustre\nis being built. Remove the autoconf tests for the presence of\n__{s,u}XX, and for the long-longiness of the primitive type used to\ndefine __u64.\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I92b0209105ee5a83df58af480c69037f2acc8973\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
